{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and the problem there was that we didn't have any documents.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only document that we had was Eve's birth certificate, but we didn't have Eve.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that wasn't a lot of good.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we basically didn't have anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I might have had my [NON-ENGLISH] from Westerbork, but that didn't do a lot of good.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Didn't have birth certificates, or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whereas, with the Russians, we couldn't speak the language.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they never even tried to interrogate us or ask our name or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the Americans, we, we could speak the language, and they had people who could speak German and Dutch, and everything really.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because by that time, which was a couple of weeks after the end of the, the war, there were Germans moving in every possible direction-- refugees, ex-army people, ex-SS people, and, and they were all pretending to be Jews from concentration camps, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And nobody knew who anybody was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, and the Americans had to sort out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we said we were Jews from Holland, kind of thing, they said, you know, prove it, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had nothing, except we could speak Dutch.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was very difficult for the Americans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they put us all into a camp, again-- in a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I never know what the English word for that is, but it's like barracks, multi-story kind of things, in an army camp, while they tried to sort us out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had loads of foods, and chewing gum, and chocolate, and all those sort of things-- probably very bad for us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and we remember being in Leipzig for several days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had rows with our fellow inmates, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
